his component will manage a single cache instance used to store and retrieve objects efficiently. 
A cache manager is a good candidate for a singleton because you want a single, 
shared cache across the entire application to ensure consistency and avoid redundant data storage.

***Single Cache Instance: Ensures that there is a single, consistent cache across the application,
which avoids duplication and ensures all parts of the application are working with the same cached data.
_____________
In this implementation, the CacheManager class uses a private constructor to initialize a cache (using a HashMap),
and provides methods to add, retrieve, remove, and clear cache entries. 
The getInstance method ensures that only one instance of the CacheManager is created and provides global access to that instanc
